issue.title: Include a proper AliasResolutionReason when multipe services are marked primary
Add ContainerFactoryTests to ensure 100% code coverage
issue.body: Both of the ContainerFactory implementations have a high code coverage % but there are a few paths in each that aren't tested. Should write enough tests to ensure 100% code coverage considering the importance of these implementations.

issue.title: Remove older class_aliases
issue.body: In #182 and #183 the codebase was organized into better namespaces and older classes deprecated. The deprecated class_alias should be removed.

issue.title: Deprecate the use of older class names

milestone.title: v2.0.0 Release
milestone.description: These are features that are useful or important but would result in an API break requiring a new major version to release.

issue.body: In #182 the codebase will be organized into cleaner namespaces. The class names that were previously used should be deprecated and marked for removal in 3.0.

issue.title: Organize classes into better namespaces
issue.body: Our current organizational structure isn't scalable and makes it hard to look through the codebase at times. We should organize the code into more descriptive namespaces. We should ensure that a `class_alias` to the existing class name is created for the new class name.

issue.title: Add option to allow certain profiles to always bust the cache
Add option to allow certain profiles to always bust the cache

comment.body: After giving this more thought I'm not sure how useful this is. Busting the cache on _every_ single test that uses the container could cause a test suite to be exceedingly slow, this has been proven in real scenarios. We need to determine a better way to bust the cache then to just say "do it everytime for this profile"

issue.title: Create an ADR for why Configuration cannot be explicitly assigned profiles
Create test to ensure alias resolution does not interfere with service delegation
issue.body: If an abstract service type has been delegated to a factory we should not attempt to resolve an alias for it. The `AliasDefinitionResolver` can be updated to include a new `AliasResolutionReason` that indicates no Alias was found because the abstract type is created by a factory.

issue.title: Add option to allow certain profiles to always bust the cache
Running build command should auto-clear cache
issue.body: The build command will erroneously re-use a cached definition if it is present. This command should clear the cache before building. Rebuilding the cached container is not intuitive and doesn't make sense.

comment.body: This will be feasible to implement once we introduce a semantic Cache instance and implementations. Right now there's no easy way to test this.

release.name: v1.3.0
release.body:
## What's Changed
* Update VERSION by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/159
* Move ActiveProfiles creation to AbstractContainerFactory by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/162
* Add event system by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/164
* Use correct dir for default directory resolver by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/167
* Include ConfigurationDefinition in serializer by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/168
* Support implicit ServiceDelegate by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/172
* Ensure enums can be injected properly by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/173
* Ensure array of enums can be injected by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/174


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/compare/v1.2.0...v1.3.0
